AFS

Flanking.minimap.db.sh
	F: Generation of an index of the reference genome assembly for mapping
	O: Flanking/minimap/sfC.ver7.mmi

Flanking.seq.tbl.pl
	F: Generation of flanking sequences of iORF-CNV and non-CNV genes
	O: Flanking/seq/tbl/*

Flanking.seq.fasta.pl
	F: Extracts flanking sequences of iORF-CNV genes
	O: Flanking/seq/fasta/*.fa

Flanking.minimap.mapping.sh
	F: performs the mapping of the flanking sequences of iORF-CNV genes against reference genomesa
	O: Flanking/minimap/mapping/*paf

nonCNV.seq.fasta.pl
	F: Extracts flanking sequences of non-CNV genes
	O: nonCNV/seq/fasta/*.fa

nonCNV.minimap.mapping.sh
	F: performs the mapping of the flanking sequences of non-CNV genes against reference genomesa
	O: nonCNV/minimap/mapping/*paf

X.nonincl.pl
	F: Finding genes of which flanking sequences are not observed from the ref genomes and finding genes that are inserted to non-genif reference genomes
	O: X/nonincl.txt
X.freq.pl
	F: Identifies genomic coordinates of the flanking sequences of the iORF-CNVs for each sample
	O: X/freq/*
X.merged.sh
	F: Identifies genomic coordinates of the flanking sequences of the iORF-CNVs from merged data across the samples
	O: X/merged/*

X.count.sh
	F: Counts the number of mapped samples for each genomic coordinates of the flanking sequences of the iORF-CNVs
	O: X/count/*

X.Ufreq.pl
	F: Identifies genomic coordinates of the flanking sequences of the non-CNVs for each sample
	O: X/Ufreq/*

X.Umerged.sh
	F: Identifies genomic coordinates of the flanking sequences of the non-CNVs from merged data across the samples
	O: X/Umerged/*

X.Ucount.sh
	F: Counts the number of mapped samples for each genomic coordinates of the flanking sequences of the non-CNVs
	O: X/Ucount/*

X.group.pl
	F: Aggregates data forom X/count/* and X/Ucount/* to classify genes based on whether they appear in multiple samples (`multi`).
	O: X/group.txt

X.fstest.R
	F: performs statistical test to see the presence of the insertion of iORF-CNVs to non-genic sequences in the reference genomes and the overrepresentation of shared insertional loci in iORF-CNVs compared with non-CNV

